In Touch Unlock mode, your lock will unlock at the press of a button as long as your phone is within range of the lock. Ranges vary based on your phone model, so if you registered the lock using one phone but wish to access it using another phone, the range may be too broad or too narrow for the other phone. Performing a device calibration will allow you to tune the range to your specific phone.

1. Your lock will light yellow to indicate a low battery.\102. Unlock and open the lock.\103. Pull the battery drawer at the bottom of lock out and remove the old battery.\104. Install a new CR2450 battery with the positive (+) side facing the back of the lock.\105. Close the battery drawer.

1. A low battery will be indicated through an email notification, the app, or by a yellow light on the lock box.\102. Unlock and open the lock box.\103. Using a flat-head screwdriver, open the battery compartment door and remove the battery.\104. Install a new CR123A battery, making sure to position the battery with positive and negative sides facing the proper direction as indicated on the battery door and inside the battery compartment. \105. Close the battery door and tighten the screw.

1. Your lock will light yellow to indicate a low battery.\102. Unlock and open the lock.\103. With back of the lock facing you, pull the bottom cover down to remove it.\104. Use a coin to turn the battery door slot 90 degrees clockwise. Open the battery door and remove the old battery.\105. Install a new CR2 battery with the positive (+) side facing right.\106. Close the battery door, and turn the slot back 90 degrees counter clockwise. Replace the bottom cover.
